
Package: lnd
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends} ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: lnd-system-mainnet
Description: Lightnning Network Daemon
 The Lightning Network Daemon (lnd) - is a complete implementation of a
 Lightning Network node. lnd has several pluggable back-end chain services
 including btcd (a full-node), bitcoind, and neutrino (a new experimental light
 client). 
 .
 Note that this is just a binary and does nothing unless configured and
 executed. Consider using lnd-system-mainnet to automatically manage the
 daemon using main Bitcoin network.

Package: lncli
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends} ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: lnd-system-mainnet
Description: Lightnning Network Daemon CLI
 lncli is a tool used for managing lnd from the command line. This package
 also contains a wrapper used to connect to the system-wide LND by default.
 You can still use --macaroonpath --rpcserver and --tlscertpath to access a
 different lnd.
